pan class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">ReadyForRatAdd</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.lean#L80-L84","name":"Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.ReadyForRupAdd","line":80,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.ReadyForRupAdd","doc":"performRupAdd adds to f.rupUnits and then clears f.rupUnits. If f begins with some units in f.rupUnits,\nthen performRupAdd will clear more than it intended to which will break the correctness of rupAdd_result.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.ReadyForRupAdd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">BVDecide</span>.<span class=\"name\">LRAT</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">ReadyForRupAdd</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.lean#L66-L78","name":"Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.limplies_of_assignmentsInvariant","line":66,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.limplies_of_assignmentsInvariant","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.limplies_of_assignmentsInvariant\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">BVDecide</span>.<span class=\"name\">LRAT</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">limplies_of_assignmentsInvariant</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f_AssignmentsInvariant</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.AssignmentsInvariant\">AssignmentsInvariant</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Entails.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.Limplies\">Limplies</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/PosFin.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.PosFin\">PosFin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.assignments\">assignments</a></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.lean#L55-L64","name":"Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.assignmentsInvariant_of_strongAssignmentsInvariant","line":55,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.assignmentsInvariant_of_strongAssignmentsInvariant","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.assignmentsInvariant_of_strongAssignmentsInvariant\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">BVDecide</span>.<span class=\"name\">LRAT</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">assignmentsInvariant_of_strongAssignmentsInvariant</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.StrongAssignmentsInvariant\">StrongAssignmentsInvariant</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.AssignmentsInvariant\">AssignmentsInvariant</a></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.lean#L42-L53","name":"Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.AssignmentsInvariant","line":42,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.AssignmentsInvariant","doc":"This invariant states that if the `assignments` field of a default formula `f` indicates that `f`\ncontains an assignment `b` at index `i`, then the unit literal `(i, b)` is entailed by `f`. This is\ndistinct from the `StrongAssignmentsInvariant` defined above in that the entailment described here\ndoes not require explicitly containing the literal `(i, b)`. For example, if `f` contains `(i, b) ∨ (j, b')`\nas well as `(i, b) ∨ (j, ¬b')`, then the `AssignmentsInvariant` would permit the `assignments` field of `f`\nto contain assignment `b` at index `i`, but the `StrongAssignmentsInvariant` would not.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.AssignmentsInvariant\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">BVDecide</span>.<span class=\"name\">LRAT</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">AssignmentsInvariant</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.lean#L30-L40","name":"Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.StrongAssignmentsInvariant","line":30,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.StrongAssignmentsInvariant","doc":"This invariant states that if the `assignments` field of a default formula `f` indicates that `f`\ncontains an assignment `b` at index `i`, then the unit literal `(i, b)` must be included in `f`.\nDefault formulas are expected to satisfy this invariant at all times except during intermediate\nstages of unit propagation (during which, default formulas are only expected to satisfy the more\nlenient `AssignmentsInvariant` defined below).\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Lemmas.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula.StrongAssignmentsInvariant\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">BVDecide</span>.<span class=\"name\">LRAT</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">DefaultFormula</span>.<span class=\"name\">StrongAssignmentsInvariant</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Tactic/BVDecide/LRAT/Internal/Formula/Implementation.html#Std.Tactic.BVDecide.LRAT.Internal.DefaultFormula\">DefaultFormula</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"}]}